    <shortlink>api http unchunk function</shortlink>
    <topic>HTTP_UNCHUNK Function</topic>
    <description>Unchunk an HTTP message body that has had a chunked transfer encoding applied.</description>
    <prototype>Message_Body as C = http_unchunk(chunked_body as C)</prototype>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>chunked_body</name>
            <type>C</type>
            <description>Original message body as received.</description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <returns>
        <return>
            <name>Message_Body</name>
            <type>C</type>
            <description>Unchunked message body.</description>
        </return>
    </returns>
    <discussion>
        <p>The HTTP_UNCHUNK() function unchunks an HTTP message body that has had a chunked transfer encoding applied to it. Some HTTP messages are sent by servers (or proxies) using a chunked transfer encoding. The full definition can be found in RFC 2616, section 3.6.1.</p>
        <p>[HTTP_GET()], [HTTP_GET_PAGE2()], [HTTP_POST()], [HTTP_POST_PAGE2()], and [HTTP_FETCH()] automatically unchunk a message.</p>
    </discussion>
